<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="Tutorial_EP17_Tarot" s="422511">
  <T n="category">422438<!--Tutorial_EP17_Category_Life&Death--></T>
  <T n="name">0x72134CA8<!--Tarot--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_Tarot_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5256c9777455379f</T>
      <T n="text">0x2AB18F06<!--Learn about <b>Tarot</b>, <b>Tarot Collecting</b>, and the <b>Order of Lenore</b> by locating the <b>Tarot Tome Shrine</b> that can be found in each neighborhood of Ravenwood. Once a Sim has interacted with this object, they are now able to find and collect <b>Tarot Cards</b> hidden throughout the world.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_Tarot_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5256c9777455379c</T>
      <T n="text">0x6F42D650<!--The Tarot Tome Shrine will reveal key Sims who are happy to reward Tarot Cards to your Sim in exchange for completing <b>Favors</b>. Cards are also hidden all over Ravenwood and can be found by exploring the <b>Crypt</b>, digging in specific areas, and using a little <b>Intuition</b>.\n\nOnce all 26 cards are collected, the deck can be created by selecting the card stack in the Sim Inventory and choosing <b>Create Deck</b>. Lady Ravendancer Goth's Tarot Deck is now complete and can be used while in the Sim's Inventory.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_Tarot_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5256c9777455379d</T>
      <T n="text">0x4C90DF41<!--If you ever get stuck searching for a card, navigate to the <b>Household Collections</b> panel, which can be found by selecting the gem icon in the Sim's Inventory. In the section marked <b>Tarot Cards</b>, hovering over an empty card slot will reveal a cryptic hint as to where this specific card can be gained.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_Tarot_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5256c9777455379a</T>
      <T n="text">0xEF043352<!--To jump right into Tarot without finding the cards, the <b>Bibbity-Basic's Tarot Deck</b> can be purchased from Build Mode. Once placed, this object can be added to a Sim's Inventory for use.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_Tarot_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5256c9777455379a</T>
      <T n="text">0x6787C35A<!--With the deck in the Sim Inventory, select the <b>Tarot Deck</b> object to complete interactions. With the <b>Bibbity-Basic's Tarot Deck</b>, a Sim can <b>Draw a Daily or Nightly Reading</b> and <b>Offer Tarot Reading</b> to others.\n\n<b>Lady Ravendancer Goth's Tarot Deck</b>, which is gained through collecting cards (and also available in the Reward Store) allows for a few extra special interactions. With this deck in a Sim's Inventory, they can also perform <b>Meditative Divination</b> which allows them to <b>Summon Lady Ravendancer</b>, perform <b>Affirmation Healing</b>, and perform <b>Divine Slumber</b> interactions.--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <T n="ui_sort_order">60</T>
</I>